'''Kudara no Konikishi Rizen''' (百済王利善) was a noble of the {{ill|Nara period|ja|奈良時代|12=draft|12=draft}}. His official Rank was {{ill|Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|ja|従四位下|lt=Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|1=Junior Fourth Rank|12=draft|12=draft}} and he held the post of {{ill|San'i no Kami|ja|散位頭|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Biography ==
In the {{ill|Empress Kōken|ja|孝謙天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}'s reign, during {{ill|Tenpyō-jingo|ja|天平神護|12=draft|12=draft}} 1 (765), he was granted the Rank of {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|12=draft|12=draft}}. In the following year, {{ill|Tenpyō-jingo|ja|天平神護|12=draft|12=draft}} 2 (766), he was appointed {{ill|Governor of Hida Province|ja|飛騨守|12=draft|12=draft}}.
During the {{ill|Emperor Kōnin|ja|光仁天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}'s reign, he served as {{ill|Assistant Governor of Sanuki Province|ja|讃岐員外介|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Hōki|ja|宝亀|12=draft|12=draft}} 2 (771). His promotions included {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|ja|従五位上|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|12=draft|12=draft}} in Hōki 7 (776), {{ill|Senior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|ja|正五位下|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|12=draft|12=draft}} in Hōki 10 (779), and {{ill|Senior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|ja|正五位上|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Ten'ō|ja|天応|12=draft|12=draft}} 1 (781). In {{ill|Enryaku|ja|延暦|12=draft|12=draft}} 2 (783), he reached the Rank of {{ill|Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|ja|従四位下|lt=Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|1=Junior Fourth Rank|12=draft|12=draft}}.
He passed away on the 24th day of the 5th month in Enryaku 3 (784). At the time of his death, his official position was {{ill|San'i no Kami|ja|散位頭|12=draft|12=draft}}.
