During the {{ill|Emperor Kōnin|ja|光仁天皇|qq=|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}'s reign, he served as {{ill|Assistant Governor of Sanuki Province|ja|讃岐員外介|qq=|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Hōki|ja|宝亀|qq=|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2 (771). His promotions included {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|ja|従五位上|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} in Hōki 7 (776), {{ill|Senior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|ja|正五位下|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} in Hōki 10 (779), and {{ill|Senior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|ja|正五位上|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Ten'ō|ja|天応|qq=|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1 (781). In {{ill|Enryaku|ja|延暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2 (783), he reached the Rank of {{ill|Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|ja|従四位下|lt=Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
He passed away on the 24th day of the 5th month in Enryaku 3 (784). At the time of his death, his official position was {{ill|San'i no Kami|ja|散位頭|qq=|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
