In the {{ill|Empress Kōken|ja|孝謙天皇|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'s reign, during {{ill|Tenpyō-jingo|ja|天平神護|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 1 (765), he was granted the Rank of {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. In the following year, {{ill|Tenpyō-jingo|ja|天平神護|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 2 (766), he was appointed {{ill|Governor of Hida Province|ja|飛騨守|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
